CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 30, 1957, p. 45, reads: "Harper's Herd - Shown are members of the Walt Harper orchestra, the swingingest group in Pittsburgh area. Left to right: Walt, pianist and leader, Jon Morris, trombone: Bert Logan Jr., drums; Nate Harper, Walt's brother, tenor saxist, and Billy Lewis, bass. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Walt Harper's band, with Walt Harper on piano, trombone player Jon Morris, drummer Bert Logan Jr., saxophone player Nate Harper, and bass player Billy Lewis, posed in interior with floral curtain in background
